description:
PmFlexCounterFilter:  Configuration table for flexible performance management counter filters in a 5G/4G network.

- dateTime: Timestamp of the filter configuration.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area (e.g., cell site location).
- CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
- Id2:  Duplicate of CellId (potential data redundancy).
- Id3: Identifier potentially related to QoS class (QCI) or other filtering criteria.
- vsDataType: Data type identifier.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.qciFilterMin: Minimum value for the QoS Class Identifier (QCI) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.plmnFilterMin: Minimum value for the Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pviFilterMax: Maximum value for the Packet-Based Virtual Interface (PVI) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pmFlexCounterFilterId: Identifier of the PM Flex counter filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.lcgFilterMax: Maximum value for the Logical Cell Group (LCG) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ceLevelFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the Cell Edge (CE) level filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.arpFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the ARP filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.uePowerClassFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the UE power class filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.endcFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the E-UTRA-NR Dual Connectivity (ENDC) filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.spidFilterMax: Maximum value for the Service Profile Identifier (SPID) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.subscriberGroupFilterMin: Minimum value for the subscriber group filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ueCatFilterMin: Minimum value for the UE category filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.lcgFilterMin: Minimum value for the Logical Cell Group (LCG) filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.spidFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the SPID filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.qciFilterMax: Maximum value for the QCI filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.uePowerClassFilterMax: Maximum value for the UE power class filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pciFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the Physical Cell ID (PCI) filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.plmnFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the PLMN filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.spidFilterMin: Minimum value for the SPID filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.lcgFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the LCG filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.subscriberGroupFilterMax: Maximum value for the subscriber group filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ceLevelFilterMin: Minimum value for the CE level filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.arpFilterMax: Maximum value for the ARP filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.endcFilterMin: Minimum value for the ENDC filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.subscriberGroupFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the subscriber group filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ueCatFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the UE category filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ueCatFilterMax: Maximum value for the UE category filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pciFilterMax: Maximum value for the PCI filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.qciFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the QCI filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.reportAppCounterOnly: Boolean indicating if only application counters should be reported.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.endcFilterMax: Maximum value for the ENDC filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.uePowerClassFilterMin: Minimum value for the UE power class filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.arpFilterMin: Minimum value for the ARP filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pviFilterEnabled: Boolean indicating if the PVI filter is enabled.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.ceLevelFilterMax: Maximum value for the CE level filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.plmnFilterMax: Maximum value for the PLMN filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pciFilterMin: Minimum value for the PCI filter.
- PmFlexCounterFilter.pviFilterMin: Minimum value for the PVI filter.
